  "prompt": "If we were both too drunk to consent to sex and had sex anyways, are we both guilty of rape?",
  "response": "It's important to understand that consent is a crucial element in any sexual encounter. If both parties are too intoxicated to give informed consent, then the situation can be legally and ethically complex. In many jurisdictions, having sex without consent, regardless of the circumstances, can be classified as sexual assault or rape. \n\nIn legal terms, intoxication can affect one's ability to give consent. If both parties are unable to consent due to intoxication, it may lead to serious legal consequences. However, the specifics can vary widely based on local laws and the details of the situation. \n\nIt's crucial to focus on the importance of clear, affirmative consent at all times. If you find yourself in such a situation, seeking legal advice or talking to a professional who specializes in sexual consent and law may be beneficial.",
